attributes.value: The single stroke roll is one of the 40 drum rudiments. This course will provide you with some speed and control exercises and also some practical drum-set applications.

The single stroke four is one of the 40 drum rudiments. This course will provide you with some practice pad exercises that will help you learn the sticking pattern, and also some practical drum-set applications.
The single stroke seven is one of the 40 drum rudiments. This course will provide you with some speed and control exercises and also some practical drum-set applications.

The double stroke roll is one of the 40 drum rudiments. This course will provide you with some practice pad exercises that will help you learn the sticking pattern, and also some practical drum-set applications.

By now, you have a good grasp on the proper grips and motions, and you have been challenged with a few exercises. We will now be shifting our focus to 3 main rudiments you want to practice on the regular. You already know the single stroke roll, and have been practicing it since you started this Learning Path (right?), so lets jump with into the double stroke roll. Do not over think your technique here right now, and just focus on getting 2 strokes per hand.

Related Lessons: Developing A Consistent Double Stroke Roll, 30 Day Double Stroke Roll Challenge, Rudiment Burn - Singles To Doubles
